      <h1 class='title'>SDA Target SDAB3</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c240WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_240ws' title='Col. 240WS &mdash; HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c240WS' name='column_240ws' href='#column_240ws' rel='bookmark'>240WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06099'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_147'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-norman-lamb' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_147' title='Link to this speech by Mr Norman Lamb' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-norman-lamb" title="Mr Norman Lamb">Norman Lamb</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06099">To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer what measures other than implementation of the <a href="/acts/financial-services-and-marketing-act">Financial Services and Marketing Act</a> were used to determine whether Spending Review 2000 SDA Target SDAB3 was met, as stated on page 20 of the HM Treasury Departmental Report 2002. [89265]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06100'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_148'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-paul-boateng' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_148' title='Link to this speech by Mr Paul Boateng' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-paul-boateng" title="Mr Paul Boateng">Mr. Boateng</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06100"> <span class="italic">[holding answer 7 January 2003]:</span> The measure used in assessing Spending Review 2000 SDA Target SDAB3 was whether the <a href="/acts/financial-services-and-markets-act-2000">Financial Services and Markets Act</a> was implemented successfully.</p><p id="S6CV0397P0-06101">The target was met on 1 December 2001 (known as N2). This was the point at which the Financial Services Authority acquired all its powers and is when the <a href="/acts/financial-services-and-markets-act-2000">Financial Services and Markets Act 2000</a> was fully implemented.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
